itle":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":54,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When William Corbucion III was born about 1170, in Studley, Warwickshire, England, his father, Peter II Corbucion, was 31 and his mother, Margaret Gifford, was 29. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Amice. He died before 1232, in his hometown."},"et":{"about 1170–before 1232":"umbes 1170–enne 1232","1159–1190":"1159–1190","1167–1203":"1167–1203","1170–1232":"1170–1232","–1227":"–1227","1175–1233":"1175–1233","1200–1255":"1200–1255","–1293":"–1293","1140–1200":"1140–1200","1142–Female":"1142–Surnud","1190":"1190","about 1170":"umbes 1170","before 1232":"enne 1232","1142":"1142","1175":"1175","1140":"1140","1293":"1293","1170":"1170","1227":"1227","1215":"1215","1203":"1203","1159":"1159","1224":"1224","1200":"1200","1255":"1255","1233":"1233","1167":"1167","1232":"1232","about 1158":"umbes 1158","Studley, Stratford-on-Avon, Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom":"Studley, Warwickshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Studley, Warwickshire, England":"Studley, Warwickshire, England","Beaudesert, Warwickshire, England":"Beaudesert, Warwickshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1170–before 1232":"noin 1170–ennen vuotta 1232","1159–1190":"1159–1190","1167–1203":"1167–1203","1170–1232":"1170–1232","–1227":"–1227","11